-- Chinese developer Evergrande 2013 net profit up 49.3 pct
-- By Clare Jim
-- Mon Mar 31, 2014 04:48AM EDT
-- None



HONG KONG, March 31 (Reuters) - China's Evergrande Real Estate Group <3333.HK> posted a 49 percent jump in full year net profit on Monday, lifted by record sales during the period.

The Guangzhou-based property developer's net profit for 2013 was 13.7 billion yuan.  Core profit last year rose 66.3 percent to 10.3 billion yuan, compared to a median forecast of 8.8 billion yuan, according to a poll by Thomson Reuters SmartEstimates.